 the first examination of Babel's life and art since the fall of communism and the opening of Soviet archives. Part biography, part history, part critical examination of the writer's legacy in Russian, European, and Jewish cultural contexts, The Enigma of Isaac Babel will be of interest to the general reader and specialist alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aAuthors, RussianxBiographyxCongressesx20th century. 0aAuthors, Russiany20th centuryvBiographyvCongresses. 0aRussian literaturexCongressesxHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aRussian literaturexCongressesxJewish authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aRussian literaturexJewish authorsxHistory and criticismvCongresses. 0aRussian literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticismvCongresses. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Russian & Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh1 aFreidin, Gregory, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804773331zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804773331423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804773331.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles